('311728592', '8/11/2013 20:18:55', 'false', '1029622444', '8/11/2013 20:07:45', 'No', '2 - 5 months', '11 - 30 min', '3 - 5 min', 'I can''t really picture this in that format, so I can''t answer this. Something tells me not a good idea.', 'My experience with Crowdflower was very good, at first. They were careful with both their instructions and answers, if I was found to be wrong. Little by little, but actually very rapidly, they went to crap, yes, crap, and the level of incompetency of this company shocks me. They constantly contradict themselves in their instructions, constantly tell you you''re wrong on the most illogical things, such as when they tell you to access a link to an account that has been closed or suspended, but when you click that button, they tell you you are wrong and what the correct answer should be. This has become the norm, and why I steer away from so many tasks now. Right now, I could point out several tasks up that are impossible to finish as set up - yet, nothing is done. There is one task they keep putting up - for MONTHS - and it is impossible to complete. If CFs clients only knew their level of incompetency, I do not think they''d be in business another week. My so-called ''accuracy'' rating was destroyed by their irrational or sloppy decisions on my "wrongness" v "rightness". So, I can''t even qualify for many tasks now. This is what is called the dumbing of America. It should be unacceptable, but it is part of an overall movement toward mediocrity that makes me depressed. So, in conclusion, the "tools" that need to be fixed to improve this platform, would be firing the employees responsible for the shoddy work against which we are measured, and replace them with thoughtful human beings with an above average IQ. Try replacing that damn Cobrain Facebook task with a verification code that actually IS correct, while you''re at it. How much simpler could it get than to cut/paste the date on which Cobrain joined Facebook - right? Well, apparently, CF disagrees with Facebook and the very precise place they directed us to go to get the info. But hey, that is the way many, if not most of the tasks go these days. You see? Get a new staff and it will be much easier for folks such as me who are actually paying attention.', '25% searching  / 75% executing', 'Yes', 'instagc'),
