('311728592', '8/12/2013 15:59:13', 'false', '1029871114', '8/12/2013 15:41:52', 'No', '1 - 3 years', '3 - 5 min', '&lt; 30 sec', 'I don''t think I''d like it.  I would have to wait for the system to "suggest" something to me, which in the long run, could mean even MORE time spent looking for a Task to complete.  I can look through a list of Tasks and click on each one much faster than waiting for an automated system.', 'I would like it very much if, when searching for a Task to do, the Task Pages would bring me BACK to where I LEFT OFF.  What I mean is, if I''m in the middle of "Page 2" of the Tasks and I click on a Task to do but find the Task has no work or that I''ve completed all I can do, I would like for the Task page to return to the MIDDLE OF PAGE 2 where I left off and NOT bring me back to the beginning of Page 1.\n\nI would also like very much if the Task Pages can HIDE Tasks that I have ALREADY COMPLETED and that have NO WORK AVAILABLE TO ME.  It''s absolutely maddening to click on the same Task day after day and have it tell you "You''ve Completed All You Can Do on This Task."  If that''s true, why does it show up in my list of Tasks?\n\nThese Tasks need to be checked for Quality Assurance.  I have had MANY Tasks, just in the past few days, that CANNOT be COMPLETED because the Task refuses the CORRECT ANSWER.  I waste my time endlessly on these Tasks thinking I can get credited after completing them and yet, I''m not able to complete them because of these errors.  Each Task needs to have a button that can let Crowd Flower know that a PAGE WAS NOT FOUND.  Many of these Tasks ask for the RANKING of the Page Found and what Page they were found on and, for many of these Tasks, the pages the Task is LOOKING for CANNOT BE FOUND, which just wastes my time AND Crowd Flower''s time because these Tasks stay in the list and no one else can complete them, either.\n\nThere has also been a very BIG problem with Tasks not accepting answers.  Example:  Task asks you to visit a Facebook page to find the phone number associated with a business.  I put in the phone number of that business which was found on that Facebook page and the Task tells me the answer is INCORRECT.  This is yet another problem where I waste my time and have to put in a "Problem" report with Crowd Flower on their website and wait to get credited.  It WORKS but, it''s sloppy and frustrating.', '87.5% searching  / 12.5% executing', 'Yes', 'fusioncash'),
